    <abstract id="aspace_aebfd6060a1a72befce6e14035e83ee3">This collection includes back-and-white photographs created by photographer N. Jay Jaffee (1921-1999). Photographs show street scenes from the Brooklyn neighborhoods of Brownsville, East New York, Coney Island, and Canarsie. The photographs were taken between 1947 and 1974, although the prints were produced at later dates. The collection also includes a bound typescript entitled, "My Father: A Reminiscence," by N. Jay Jaffee (1994).</abstract>
